The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval (PIR) over a distributed storage system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of MDS codes in the storage system suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), and computer networks (cs.CC). The focus on minimizing implementation complexity suggests a possible connection to systems and control (cs.SI).
